GXLGraph, GXLGraphElement
public abstract class GXLTypedElement
extends GXLAttributedElement

Superclass for all GXLElements that can be typed using the type element.

GXLTypedElements can be typed by adding a type element containing a link to a GXLSchema element that describes the type.

See Also:
GXLType

getType

public GXLType getType()
Returns the type of this element, or null if no type is specified. This method simply checks if a GXLType child exists, returning it if so.

Returns:
The type of this element, or null if no type is specified.
See Also:
GXLElement.getChildAt(int i)

setType

public void setType(URI uri)
Sets the type of this element. This method checks if a GXLType child already exists, changing it's uri if so. Otherwise a new GXLType is created and added to this element.

Parameters:
uri - The URI specifying the GXLSchema element that types this element.
